  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Testing BRCA 1/2 mutation is important for patients with breast cancer, and Sanger sequencing
      is a standard method to identify BRCA 1/2 mutation. Next generation sequencing (NGS) is a
      high-throughput parallel sequencing that can provide genetic information with high accuracy.
      NGS is a faster and cost-effective method to detect gene mutations compared to Sanger
      sequencing. In this study, we evaluated the clinical role of NGS testing for BRCA 1/2
      compared to Sanger sequencing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
